<br>
To that end they have to make the stuff a challenge. Not that I think the way the crap is now is right. I'm just saying the whole point of that crap is to keep you on as much as possible. All their bull@#%$ about wanting to make the game as enjoyable as possible may be true from a few people at Verant's view, but is surely not the bottom line. Funny, most of the time I think they only make some stuff fun because they know it has to be fun to make people want to come back <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
It is kinda screwy. Were mages included in that stupid message about some of the FA quests being on hold for the DirectX enchancement crap? I didn't think we were, but it would not surprise me in the least.<br>
<br>
And, in reference the Rogue comment...<br>
1. If the Rogue quest IS actually easier, GREAT! I have a 20th lvl Rogue on Rodcet, and a baby 7th on Fennin. Rogues got the bigest shaft of any class for the longest time by far. You really can't argue that at all (usless skills, no real reason for groups to want them, etc...) so I'll move on <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Yes they have seen some improvements, but none of them have made Rogues what they wanted to be (exactly how many meaningfull traps, and locks are there in the game? etc...) it's all been an effort to distract Rogues from the meaningfull stuff they wanted. They do it to all the classes, and I can honestly understand their views somewhat(they would have to double or tripple their programing staff to make half the proposed changes everyone wants and people still would be unhappy).<br>
<br>
2. The Rogue community as a whole is MUCH closer knit than the Mage (well hell, ANY other) community is. There are entire Rogue only guilds on every server. I can't say for sure, but I bet that is not true for any other class. That is one positive effect of Verant screwing the rogues for so long. That and fact that Rogue guilds were most common along with merchant guilds in almost every fantasy setting I have ever read.<br>
<br>
Because of those two reasons it wouldn't surprise me either way to see 6 Rogues teaming together for 8 hours a night for a straight week to be the first to have Burning Rapiers (is that the quest you were talking about?). I cant tell from your message but I think 40-50+ hours from six DEVOTED people (like any Rogue that has topped 50 MUST be, that or twinked/power leveled out the butt) and you might see the Magi quest solved, or at least the fact that it is broken proven. <br>
<br>
If it was the BR quest you were talking about, I myself have spent well over 12 hours (2 sessions of about 6 hours) killing gnoll commanders, and elites and never recieved 1 stupid Gnoll Skin. Dozens of Gnoll pelts. Two rusty spiked shoulderpads 2gazillion earings/spiked collars/studded collars, and quite a bit of the weird drops (like one of about every non rare gem in the game).<br>
<br>
I think the big problem is in the way computers handle random occurences. Some things in the game should be hard, but not completely random like they are <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I'm reminded of people trying to get one specific card in Magic to complete a set, opening 3 boxes (almost 120 packs) and never getting all of the rares (30-70 in a set one per pack. breaks down to 75% chance in small sets, 50% in bigger sets). They have assigned numbers to things that should not be numericaly controlled <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I mean honestly, how many of us randomly decide whether or not to carry our wallets? How about which car to drive to work? Okay, now how much sense is there for a caster type dude that lives in the water to not have his staff with him? Thats like killing an accountant and them not dropping a pen or a PDA or a calculator <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Random drop camp quests need to go away. It's stupid that they have to resort to such boring methods to keep people online. I personaly have had much more fun on active quests like the Langseax of the Wolves quest as opposed to camping the stupid Glowing Black Stone from Pyzjn or the mother of all stupidity for us mages: Journeymans Boots. Crap! Why not just put the stupid boots on a merchant and have them cost 20,000 Plat and put that merchant 3 zones from the nearest bank <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Or OMG actually make it a roleplaying thing where you actually have to journey to get them? Like you have to visit all of the gnomes cousins and ferry notes or some crap like that. Noooooo they have to make some stupid Rare drop rare spawn, or overcamped static spwan crap.<br>
<br>
It just shows a blatant lack of creativity from Verant. All they did is make it more of a pain and reduced the traffic to Najena? (that was where they used to drop right?) Instead people camp the hell out of the AC in OOT. How the hell much different is that?<br>
<br>
For some obviously bright and creative people, Verant as a whole sure pulls some stupid repetitive crap out of their butts.<br>
<br>
&quot;The Vision&quot; my ass! The only &quot;Vision&quot; that Verant has is of $$$ in front of their eyes <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Thanks for your time reading this, it felt good to vent a little <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
